                <div class="doc-check">✓</div>
                <div>
                  <strong>Recent pay stubs — last 3 to 6 months</strong>
                  <p>Shows your current income level, especially important if your tax return is outdated or low.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="doc-item">
                <div class="doc-check">✓</div>
                <div>
                  <strong>Employer letter on company letterhead</strong>
                  <p>Must include your name, job title, start date, employment status (full-time or part-time), and annual salary or hourly rate. Must be signed by HR or a manager.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="doc-item">
                <div class="doc-check">✓</div>
                <div>
                  <strong>Self-employment: Schedule C from tax return + business bank statements</strong>
                  <p>If self-employed, attach Schedule C showing net profit, 12 months of business bank statements, and any business license.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="doc-cat">
            <div class="doc-cat-header">
              <div class="doc-cat-icon">🏦</div>
